<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<package xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/packaging/2010/07/nuspec.xsd">
  <metadata>
    <id>MegaForm.Oqtane</id>
    <version>1.7.101</version>
    <authors>MegaForm Team</authors>
    <owners>MegaForm</owners>
    <title>MegaForm - Dynamic Form Builder</title>
    <description>Dynamic Form Builder for Oqtane — drag-and-drop form designer with templates, multi-step forms, conditional logic, payment widgets, rules engine, and submissions management.</description>
    <copyright>MegaForm Team</copyright>
    <requireLicenseAcceptance>false</requireLicenseAcceptance>
    <license type="expression">MIT</license>
    <projectUrl>https://github.com/nicknguyen-oqtane/MegaForm</projectUrl>
    <icon>icon.png</icon>
    <tags>oqtane module form builder survey payment</tags>
    <releaseNotes>v1.7.101 (20260711) — 🔐 ROLE/PERMISSION FIELD VISIBILITY (server-enforced) + 🖥️ Access UI + AI guardrail. (1) 🔐 SERVER-SIDE FIELD PROJECTION: a field restricted to a role (a `showIf` rule whose leaf has `sourceType:"Role"|"Permission"|"User"|"Query"`) is now REMOVED from the schema before it reaches the browser, on the public form path of ALL three platforms (Oqtane `Schema/{formId}` + `render/{formId}` + the Index.razor prerender snapshot; Web `Submit/Schema`; DNN `Submit/Schema` + `FormView.ascx` SSR). Previously such a field was still shipped and merely CSS-hidden — readable with curl. NEW `MegaForm.Core` services: `RuleStaticEvaluator` (three-valued Kleene evaluation at render time; anything it cannot prove stays HIDDEN — fail-closed, the opposite of `SharedRuleEngine`'s intentionally permissive submit-time default) and `FormSchemaVisibilityFilter` / `FormAccessProjection.ProjectForActor` (strips denied fields + role leaves from BOTH the mirrored `fields`/`Fields` arrays a resolved schema carries; holders of the `manage` permission are bypassed so admins still see everything). Fast path: a form with no `sourceType` and no field restrictions returns the exact same string — its public HTML is byte-identical, verified. (2) 🛡️ SUBMIT ENFORCEMENT: the real actor is now threaded into the submit pipeline on Web (`Submit/Post`) and DNN (`SubmitController.Post` → `ProcessSubmissionAsync`), so `EnforceSubmit` evaluates role rules against the visitor's actual roles instead of stripping role-gated fields for everyone (previously null-actor). A non-authorized POST of a hidden field is stripped before persistence; readonly field restrictions now RESTORE the database value on edit instead of blanking it. (3) 🖥️ ACCESS TAB UI: the builder's Permissions &amp; Access tab gains a "Field visibility by role" table (tick the roles that may see each field → writes the server-enforced `showIf` role rule) and an "Expand" button that opens the full 7-column permission matrix + field-visibility in a large centered popup (the matrix was clipped in the narrow right rail). (4) 🤖 AI GUARDRAIL: a `prompt_rule` KB entry teaches the AI that role/permission visibility is access control (Access tab / `showIf` role rule), not a client form rule; the form-rule validator now returns actionable guidance instead of a confusing rejection when a role leaf is attempted. AssetVersion→20260711-B392 (builder + ai-form-assistant bundles rebuilt). Carries v1.7.100.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.100 (20260710) — 🩹 ADVANCED-FILTER POPOVERS VISIBLE IN FULLSCREEN + 💾 PERSISTED PRESETS + 🌐 i18n. (1) 🩹 The "All fields", "+ Add filter", "Presets" and filter-chip popovers were INVISIBLE whenever the admin panel ran in its fullscreen surface (`.mf-oq-surface.is-fs` = `position:fixed; z-index:10000`): the popover is portaled into `&lt;body&gt;` and painted at `z-index:1200`, so it was created at the right coordinates but covered by the opaque surface — the buttons looked dead, with no console error. Headless QA never saw it because fullscreen is an opt-in preference persisted in `localStorage['mf-surface-fs']`, so a clean automation profile always renders the inline surface. The popover now paints at `z-index:200000` (above the surface, below the `200001+` modal tier that the detail sheet already used) with `position:fixed` viewport coordinates — the previous absolute+`window.scrollY` math was wrong anyway, because in fullscreen the surface scrolls, not the window. It also flips above the anchor when it would overflow the viewport bottom (the fullscreen surface is exactly viewport-tall, so an overflowing popover could never be scrolled into view). (2) 💾 PRESETS NOW PERSIST: saved filter presets lived only in module state and were lost on every reload. They are stored in `localStorage['mf-subs-presets-v1']` as a bucket-per-form map, mirroring the existing `mf-subs-columns-v4` column store so one form's presets can never reference another form's fields; a corrupt/hand-edited entry is rejected rather than crashing the toolbar, the built-in "New submissions" preset is regenerated (so its name follows the active locale) rather than stored, and each user preset gains a delete button. (3) 🌐 The whole advanced-filter surface is localized — 44 keys (`subs.advf.*`, including every operator label: contains / is exactly / before …) across 18 locales (en-US + the 11 maintained + es/fr/ja/ko/vi/zh). This also closes 4 keys (`subs.filtered_count`, `subs.filtered_count_hint`, `subs.col_submitted_by`, `subs.col_device`) that v1.7.99 referenced but never added to en-US. AssetVersion→20260710-B383 (megaform-submissions + megaform-i18n bundles + megaform-submissions-ts.css rebuilt). Carries v1.7.99.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.99 (20260710) — 🔎 SUBMISSIONS ADVANCED FILTER + PRESETS (submission-advanced-filter.ts). The submissions inbox toolbar gains a mock-parity multi-field filter builder: an "All fields" search-scope selector inside the search box, a "+ Add filter" popover (grouped field picker → operator → value) that adapts to the form's REAL response fields + metadata (Submitted By/Date/Status/Device-from-user-agent/Form/ID), editable filter chips, and a "Presets" popover (save/load filter configurations). A "Status is X" filter is pushed to the SERVER (filters all rows, correct pagination — verified 500000→49860 on a 500K form); field-value filters / scoped search / date-range refine the loaded page client-side with an honest "N of M on this page" badge; an empty-value filter is blocked (Apply disabled) so it never blanks the table. AssetVersion→20260710-B382 (megaform-submissions bundle + megaform-submissions-ts.css rebuilt). Carries v1.7.98.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.98 (20260707) — 🎫 Trial form limit raised 3 → 10. The trial (unlicensed) form-count cap is now 10 forms (was 3); `LicenseService.MaxTrialForms` = 10. The server returns the limit dynamically in the 402 response and every message, so no UI change was needed — the trial site now allows up to 10 forms before SaveForm returns 402 "Trial mode is limited to 10 forms." Production (license.lic="production") remains unlimited. Submission cap per form (25) unchanged. No JS/CSS change (AssetVersion stays 20260707-B380). Carries v1.7.97.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.97 (20260707) — 🖼️ Template visual polish (live-test round 2): map integration, step-bar responsiveness, outback rhythm, standard-field spacing. (1) 🗺️ CONTACT-MAP templates (left-corporate / left-minimal / right-modern) no longer paint an ugly light-gray outer band that floated detached on a dark host page — the outer wrapper + `.mf-bg` are now transparent by default (`var(--mf-preset-bg, transparent)`) so the map + form-card sit directly on the page like the mock, and the card/contact-info surfaces are wired to the preset channel (`var(--mf-preset-surface, original)`, tint-preserving color-mix) so a picked theme preset recolors them; byte-identical with no preset. (2) 🪜 PROJECT-INTAKE step bar no longer horizontally scrolls on desktop (the rail's `min-width:max-content` forced it wider than the card) and no longer overflows on mobile — below 640px it collapses to a compact numbered-dot row showing only the active step's label (mirrors the mock). (3) 🏜️ OUTBACK (classic-australiana) stepper + hero→form vertical rhythm pixel-matched to the mock: the shell's `!important` resets on generic `ol/li/h*/p` tags had crammed the step pills (24px tall, indented) and collapsed the stepper→title→intro spacing; the template now re-asserts roomy pills (36px, left-aligned to the title), 28px stepper gap, and the correct title/intro rhythm at a higher specificity. (4) 📐 STANDARD (wizard/plain) forms get more breathing room to match the clean-card mocks: `--mf-field-gap` 12→16px (field→field + 2-col gap), `--mf-label-margin-bottom` 6→8px, `--mf-label-font-weight` 600→500 (font-medium like the mock). These are canonical `:root` tokens read by both SSR + client renderers; premium/custom shells set their own field/label styling so they are unaffected (shipped premium templates do not reference `--mf-field-gap`). AssetVersion→20260707-B380 (megaform.css changed). Carries v1.7.96.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.96 (20260707) — 🎨 Preset channel end-to-end on dark templates + 🪜 step-bar reconcile + 🧊 stale module-CSS overlay fix. (1) 🎨 DARK TEMPLATE FULL RECOLOR: the event-registration-rsvp template painted its page/panel/inputs through INTERNAL tone vars (`--mf-rsvp-bg/panel/text/muted/line` + `var(--mf-bg/--mf-surface, hex)` fallbacks) that never referenced the preset channel — a Theme preset changed accents/inputs but the page stayed black. Every tone var and inline white/amber alpha is now chained to `--mf-preset-{bg,surface,text,primary,on-primary}` (alpha tones via `color-mix(in srgb, var(--mf-preset-*, original) N%, transparent)`, which resolves to the EXACT original rgba when no preset is active) — no preset = byte-identical dark design, preset = the whole template recolors readably (verified: emerald on :5118, slate on :5117, and a forced no-preset fallback measures the original hexes). (2) 🎛️ The builder Theme-Designer PRESETS RAIL (theme-left-rail) never emitted the `--mf-preset-*` channel (only the ⚙ Settings popup did) — rail presets recolored accents but never template surfaces; the rail's Apply now mirrors the settings-popup preset-channel mapping. (3) 🪜 STEP-BAR RECONCILE: deleting a page break in the builder on a premium-native form merges the PAGES correctly, but the decorative step rail is static customHtml — the dead step stayed visible ("4 steps" on a 3-page form) and the last step could never activate. New renderer module `premium-step-reconcile.ts` maps schema pages back to rail items via the surviving Sections' `premiumStepIndex` (1-based), hides exactly the deleted step (keeping every surviving step's own label), renumbers the visible numerals ordinally, trims connector lines, and remaps active/done highlighting — a strict no-op when rail items == pages (all stock templates). (4) 🧊 STALE MODULE-CSS OVERLAY ([B262] closure): the per-module `MegaForm:ModuleStyleJson` snapshot copied the form's `customCss` when the ⚙ settings popup seeded it, and `OverlayModuleStyle` then made that STALE copy WIN over the form's live CSS on the public page — builder CSS/image edits (e.g. a changed hero image) never showed until the snapshot was hand-deleted. The snapshot no longer stores or overlays `customCss` (theme + var-map style fields only); existing sites heal in place because the overlay skips any old copies. AssetVersion→20260707-B379 (renderer + builder + settings-popup bundles rebuilt). Carries v1.7.95.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.95 (20260707) — 🧑‍💻 Live-test feedback round. (1) 🔘 NO-FLASH STEP BUTTONS: premium-native multi-step shells baked all three action buttons (Back/Next/Submit) visible into the SSR markup and only the JS renderer hid Back+Submit for step 0 — on slow loads all three flashed. `RenderCustomHtml` now bakes the step-0 state server-side (`hidden` + display:none on `[data-mf-native-back]`/`[data-mf-native-submit]` when the shell has ≥2 native pages); the client `setButtonState` re-syncs both directions on every step change. (2) 🪜 STEPPER INDEX null-fix (renderer): `Number(getAttribute('data-step'))` treats a MISSING attribute as 0 (`Number(null)===0`), so any template whose stepper items carry no explicit index rendered EVERY step as active; missing/empty attributes now fall back to DOM order (AssetVersion 20260707-B378). (3) ✏️ HERO TEXT EDITING: the Design-tab Text-style panel opened on FOCUS, landing on top of the text the author had just clicked to edit; focus now shows a small floating style trigger instead and the panel opens only on demand — typing works immediately. (4) 🎨 PRESET SURFACE on dark templates: Theme-Designer presets recolored only text/primary on the dark event-registration-rsvp template because its page/panel backgrounds were hardcoded hex; they now follow the preset channel (`var(--mf-preset-surface/bg, original)`) — identical without a preset, fully recolored with one. Carries v1.7.94 —⚡ SSR first-load smoothness + 🎨 premium template mock-parity. (1) ⚡ SSR SNAPSHOT PREWARM: on an Interactive-rendermode site, the FIRST soft-nav (enhanced-nav click) to a form page missed the SsrSnapshot cache (5-min TTL, warmed only by a prior render of that page) → the interactive _loading render showed the FastPaint skeleton ("wireframe") for ~1.4s and the JS renderer rebuilt the form client-side. The existing loopback warmup service now also sweeps the site's own /sitemap.xml and prerenders every page once at startup (capped, fail-soft), so every form's snapshot is warm from the first click; the snapshot TTL is raised 5min→6h (it self-refreshes on every completed load, so a form edit is stale for under a second before the fresh render replaces it). (2) 🔇 The renderer's unconditional "MegaForm: rendering N fields" console line printed even on SSR bind-only hydrates, reading like a phantom client rebuild; it now logs only on the real client-build path (AssetVersion 20260707-B377). (3) 🎨 TEMPLATE MOCK-PARITY (curated set, template-only): euro-youth — a historic edit LOST an `@media(min-width:640px){` header in customCss leaving an orphan brace that broke browser CSS parsing from that point (the 1024px block never applied → the LEFT HERO PANEL never showed); header restored (hero photo/brand/stats panel + 440px split shell now render), all six profile fields paired into the mock's 2-column grid, Duration+Preferred-start paired, hero H1 forced white (a shell h1 override repainted it dark), right panel solid stone like the mock. bulgaria — every stepper item was rose/"active" because the steps carried no data-step index (the premium stepper sync reads Number(getAttribute)=Number(null)=0 → every step matched page 0); steps/lines are now indexed (01 active + rest gray, done=rose fill+check, passed connectors rose), and Phone+DOB, Gender+Nationality, Experience+Languages, Duration+Accommodation are paired 2-column with an even 18px row rhythm. down-under (australia) — connector lines indexed, Phone+DOB and Duration+Stay paired 2-column. Carries v1.7.93 —🛡️ Fixed-header overlap guard + 📐 in-field row rhythm + 🕐 native Time input. (1) 🛡️ FIXED-HEADER GUARD: host themes that paint their site header as a position:fixed/sticky bar (e.g. Oqtane's default theme) can COVER the top of the form card when the bar grows taller than the offset the theme reserves for content — the nav menu wraps to extra rows on sites with many pages, the logged-in control row appears, or the window is narrow; the card's rounded top / hero / title slid underneath the bar (and login vs logout looked different, because the admin module-actions row shifts the module down while also making the bar taller). A theme cannot be fixed from inside a module, so the renderer now measures the shortfall at runtime (NEW `src/renderer/fixed-header-guard.ts`: finds the fixed/sticky full-width bar pinned to the viewport top, compares its painted bottom to the module's resting document position) and pushes ONLY the MegaForm module container down by exactly that amount, re-measuring after layout settles and on window resize. Sites without a fixed header, or without overlap, are a strict no-op; popup/preview surfaces are excluded. (2) 📐 IN-FIELD ROW SPACING: the vertical gap between rows INSIDE a composite field was a hardcoded 8px while top-level fields moved to the 12px `--mf-field-gap` rhythm in v1.7.92 — in-field rows now use `gap:var(--mf-field-gap, 12px)` in BOTH renderers (client TS + server SSR), matching the top-level spacing and following ⚙ Settings → Field spacing; the horizontal gap between cells in one row stays 8px. (3) 🕐 NATIVE TIME FIELD: `type:"Time"` (used by ~25 stock templates — pure-grid contact, contact-us-standard, winter-row-based, the RTL set) had NO case in either renderer and fell through to the widget-plugin branch, showing a yellow "Widget Time — plugin not installed" placeholder on the public form; both renderers now emit a native `&lt;input type="time" class="mf-input"&gt;`. AssetVersion→20260707-B376 (renderer bundle rebuilt). Carries v1.7.92.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.92 (20260706) — 🌐 Designer i18n + 📐 field-spacing + 🔀 anon-form-binding fix. (1) 🌐 The builder's field/token DESIGNER modals (Composite/Input Designer, Slider, Map, Image-Choice, Video, and the shared token-designer shell) were 100% hardcoded English while the rest of the builder (Wizard, Settings) was localized. All ~150 user-facing strings are now wrapped in a shared `wt(key, fallback)` i18n helper (`src/builder/designer-i18n.ts`) under the `des.*` key namespace and added to the canonical catalog, with translations shipped for 7 languages (Vietnamese, Spanish, French, German, Chinese-Simplified, Japanese, Portuguese-BR); the remaining locales carry English placeholders (fill via the in-product Translate-AI tool). (2) 📐 FIELD SPACING: `--mf-field-gap` reduced 20px→12px. The label-above already gives each top-level field ~27px of separation (matching the composite sub-rows' label-below rhythm); the extra 20px flex gap stacked on top made top-level fields sit ~47px apart (input→input) versus ~27px inside a composite — visually "too tall" and inconsistent. 12px tightens top-level to ~39px, much closer to the composite (still user-adjustable via ⚙ Settings → Field spacing). (3) 🔀 FIX "same form shows differently logged-in vs logged-out": the Oqtane module renders static-SSR always; the admin path reads the module→form binding FRESH from the DB (via the admin-only GetModuleConfig), but the anonymous path gets 403 and falls back to `ModuleState.Settings` — Oqtane's IMemoryCache — which stayed STALE after a rebind because `SaveForm`'s auto-bind wrote the DB setting without calling `InvalidateSiteSettingsCache()` (unlike SaveStyle/SaveModuleStyle/SaveModuleConfig). So a form rebound from A→B kept rendering the OLD form to anonymous visitors until an app restart. `SaveForm` now invalidates the cache on rebind. AssetVersion→20260706-B375 (builder + megaform.css rebuilt). Carries v1.7.91.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.91 (20260706) — 🧾 SUBMISSION readability + multi-choice data-loss fixes (audit-driven). A live QA (AI-built form with Phone/Address Composite, Chips, Rating, Signature) + a 30-agent code audit found the submission value pipeline was not uniformly human-readable and that multi-select Chips/Cards SILENTLY DROPPED selections. Fixes: (1) 🐛 DATA-LOSS: `getFieldValue` (renderer `conditional.ts`, which `collectFormData` delegates to) had a branch only for Checkbox — Chips (checkbox-skinned, multi) and Cards (radio-skinned) fell through to the generic `[name=key]` selector and collected only the FIRST option's value, so a user picking 3 chips submitted 1. Now a DOM-kind-aware branch collects ALL checked values for checkbox-skinned choices (array) and the single checked value for radio-skinned. (2) `MegaFormUtils.ToRawString` emitted the .NET type-name `System.Collections.Generic.List\`1[System.Object]` into the submission snapshot `RawValue` (shown in the submissions LIST columns / CSV) for a multi-value field, because Oqtane's STJ submit normalizes JSON arrays to a CLR `List&lt;object&gt;` and the method fell through to `raw.ToString()`; it now serializes collections to JSON (`["music","food"]`). (3) `SubmissionIndexerService.ProjectValue` (the Reports/SQL flat index `ValueText`) had the same `Convert.ToString` defect → now flattens collections to a comma-joined value string. (4) `MegaFormUtils.ToDisplayString` had no branch for Signature/Payment/File/DataGrid → the DisplayValue (Summary column, email, CSV, PDF, and the Details envelope) showed a raw base64 data-URL or raw JSON blob; now renders a short human summary (`[signature]`, `USD 10 · paid · txn …`, filename list, `N rows`) while the client Details tab still renders the image/links from the raw DataJson. (5) The client "Data View" tab now maps static Radio/Select/Checkbox/Chips/Cards option VALUES → LABELS in its read-only display (editable inputs keep the raw value so save round-trips). NOTE: the everyday submission Details **summary panel** was already human-readable in 1.7.90 (it reads the envelope `DisplayValue` which maps labels + joins composites) — these fixes harden the LIST columns / Reports / CSV / email / genuine multi-Checkbox surfaces + stop the Chips data-loss. AssetVersion→20260706-B374 (renderer + submissions bundles rebuilt). Carries v1.7.90.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.90 (20260706) — 🧩 RULES-ENGINE now LIVE on public forms + 🖼️ widget hydration + 🎠 slider edge fix + 📇 gallery icon fix + upload/card polish + KB. (1) ⭐ FORM-LEVEL RULES (settings.rules / RulesJson) were DEAD on the public renderer — only per-field `showIf` (`data-show-if`) worked; the `when/then/else` rules authored in the builder (conditional show/hide/require + `setValue`) never ran once a form was published. The ACTIVE renderer (src/renderer/index.ts → megaform-renderer.js) now wires `MegaFormRules.evaluateRules(settings.rules, formData)` at every hydrate chokepoint (`bindRuleEngine`), applying effects to `.mf-field-group[data-key]` groups, and a `setValue` whose value starts with `=` is evaluated as an arithmetic FORMULA over sibling field-keys (`= number_of_people * nights * 2000000`; safe-eval, only `[0-9+-*/().%]`). So "show room-type only when traveling with family" and "total = people × nights × rate" work on the live form. Verified on :5115 form 17 (checkbox `isNotEmpty` toggles a field; people=4→8,000,000 / people=7→14,000,000). ⚠️ A single-option Checkbox trigger must use operator `isNotEmpty` (its value is an array — `isTrue` never matches). (2) 🖼️ WIDGET FIELDS (ContentSlider, QR, payment, phone-pro) rendered as EMPTY hosts on SSR-hydrated forms — SSR emits an empty `[data-mf-widget-hydrate]` placeholder and the old bind pass only attached events, never filled it. New `bindWidgetsSafe` calls `renderWidget(field)` into each empty host before binding, so widgets actually appear. (3) 🎠 Content-Slider drag over-scroll: swiping PAST the first/last slide slid the track into empty space (a blank panel). `applyTransform` now rubber-bands the over-drag (damped to 22%); release still snaps to a valid slide. (4) 📇 TEMPLATE GALLERY icon bug: template-level icons in the curated set are lucide-style NAMES (`compass`, `sparkles`, `globe-2`, `flower-2`) which are not glyphs — the wizard Setup grid (step-setup), builder gallery (gallery.ts) and its search patch printed the raw NAME as text next to the template title. All three now render a neutral FontAwesome glyph for non-`fa-` names (matching the gallery-modal guard); `fa-*` classes and emoji/symbols still render. (5) ⬆️ Upload control SSR parity: the file dropzone server markup now matches the mock (upload-arrow icon + "Drop files here or click to upload" + a size/type hint, all HTML-encoded). (6) 🃏 Option-card unselected state now shows a bordered outline instead of `opacity:0` (matched to the mock). (7) 📇 AI KB: +2 `form_pattern` seed entries (boolean/yes-no field must render a control + be a valid rule trigger; `setValue` `= expr` calc), so the AI stays on-rails when adding conditional/calc logic — 323 seed entries. AssetVersion→20260706-B373 (renderer + dashboard + builder + slider-plugin bundles rebuilt). Carries v1.7.89.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.89 (20260706) — 🔐 AUTH template → GitHub + Facebook + click-404 FIX, and 📦 template gallery replaced with the 16 curated DONEE templates. (1) The Member Login template (`member-login`) now offers **Continue with GitHub** + **Continue with Facebook** (was Google + GitHub) — both are Oqtane oauth2 presets. Core already had `AuthProviders.Facebook`; Index.razor now also publishes `__MF_PLATFORM__.auth.facebook` (added to BOTH the public `BuildRendererBootScript` and the builder boot block). (2) 🔧 FIX: clicking an auth button navigated to `/404`. The buttons are `&lt;a href="/pages/external?…"&gt;` and `/pages/external` / `/signin-oauth2` are server-side Razor Pages, NOT Blazor routes — Blazor's enhanced navigation intercepted the internal `&lt;a&gt;` click, found no client route, and redirected to `/404` (a real 200 Oqtane page, so `fetch()`-based checks missed it; only a real click reproduced). The template's `auth_wire` customScript now sets `data-enhance-nav="false"` and attaches a capture-phase handler that does `preventDefault();stopImmediatePropagation();window.location.assign(href)` — forcing a full-document navigation that correctly hits the endpoint (403 until an external provider is configured, then a 302 to the provider). QA-verified on :5114 (network-confirmed `GET /pages/external?…&amp;provider=GitHub|Facebook → 403`, no /404). (3) 📦 The shipped Template Gallery (wwwroot/Modules/MegaForm/Templates) was replaced with the 16 curated DONEE templates: adds `v0-contact-map-left-corporate`, `v0-contact-map-left-minimal`, `v0-contact-map-right-modern`, `pure-grid-template`, `vendor-application`; the previous 11 are the same templates (5 were just renamed files, byte-identical). All 16 validated (unique slugs, valid field types); a clean install seeds all 16 into App_Data. AssetVersion unchanged (no JS/CSS bundle change; template + Client-DLL only). Carries v1.7.88.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.88 (20260706) — 🔐 AUTH: platform-agnostic host auth URL seam + a Member Login template with Google/GitHub social sign-up. NEW Core `IAuthUrlProvider` (LoginUrl/RegisterUrl/ExternalLoginUrl(provider)/IsAuthenticated) + `AuthProviders` constants — the cross-platform seam so ONE login template works on Oqtane/DNN/Umbraco/Web (MegaForm never authenticates; it hands off to the host login + external-login flow). Oqtane impl `OqtaneAuthUrlProvider` (verified routes: `/login`, `/register`, `/pages/external?returnurl=` — the last 403s until an External Login provider is configured under Admin → User Management; Oqtane supports ONE site-wide external provider). Index.razor now publishes `window.__MF_PLATFORM__.auth = {login,register,external,google,github,currentUrl,isAuthenticated}`. NEW premium template `member-login` (custom-HTML login card; Google + GitHub buttons carry `[data-mf-auth]`; a managed customScript sets their href from `__MF_PLATFORM__.auth` and survives the custom-shell rebuild). To complete a REAL sign-in the site owner must register OAuth apps (Google Cloud / GitHub Dev) and configure Oqtane external login (config-only). Core+Server+Client DLLs changed → ModuleInfo.Version→1.7.88 (AssetVersion unchanged, no JS/CSS bundle change). Carries v1.7.87.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.87 (20260706) — 🎨 PRESET WIRE + Outback template polish. (1) NEW dedicated preset colour channel `--mf-preset-*` (primary/text/surface/accent/border/bg/on-primary): emitted scoped to the form wrapper ONLY when a theme preset/override is active (server `ThemeFirstPaintCssService` [PresetWire] + client `settings-popup` parity). Unlike `--mf-primary`/`--mf-text`/`--mf-form-bg`/`--mf-border` — which the base CSS sets GLOBALLY so `var(--mf-primary, orig)` always resolves to the global value and a template can never tell "no preset" from "preset=default" — `--mf-preset-*` has NO global default. Premium templates derive identity from `var(--mf-preset-primary, &lt;own colour&gt;)`: absent → own colour (identity preserved byte-for-byte), preset picked → recolour. Purely additive (new var names); existing forms unaffected. (2) Outback template (classic-australiana-booking) pixel-matched to the mock: form controls render cream `#fffdf7` / 1px tan `#d9c7a6` / 10px / 47px / 14px (the template's bare `input[type=…]` rules lost to the shell `.mf-input`; fixed by SETTING `--mf-input-bg/border/radius` on the wrapper so CustomShellCompat resolves them) + choice cards cream + nav button 14px; and wired to the new preset channel. wwwroot outback synced to the converted+fixed DONEE. ⚠️ ModuleStyleJson gotcha: editing a form's SchemaJson.customCss via SaveForm does NOT refresh the per-module `MegaForm:ModuleStyleJson` snapshot (B262) that `OverlayModuleStyle` makes WIN on the public module page — delete/reseed it after out-of-band CSS edits. AssetVersion→20260706-B372. Carries v1.7.86.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.86 (20260705) — 🛡️ FIX double-submit on premium multi-step forms. A premium-native custom submit button is reached by TWO submit paths in a single click: the fields-container delegated `button[type=submit]` handler (bindSubmit) AND the premium-native proxy that forwards the click to the hidden native `#mf-btn-submit` → both call doSubmit() synchronously in the same tick → TWO POST /Submit/Post requests → TWO duplicate submission rows per submit (verified on :5114: wellness/down-under/rsvp each created 2 submissionIds from one click; a payment form would double-charge). FIX = a re-entrancy guard in the renderer (`submitInFlight`): set right before the XHR POST and cleared on `onloadend`, so the second synchronous doSubmit() bails. Does NOT block the legitimate review→confirm sequence (the review path returns before the flag is set) nor a later "Submit another". Renderer JS only (src/renderer/index.ts → megaform-renderer.js); AssetVersion→20260705-B371. Verified: one click → exactly ONE POST, thank-you pane intact, across both the native (`data-mf-native-page`) and template (`data-step` au/bg/ey/fi) step mechanisms. Carries v1.7.85. A premium-native custom submit button is reached by TWO submit paths in a single click: the fields-container delegated `button[type=submit]` handler (bindSubmit) AND the premium-native proxy that forwards the click to the hidden native `#mf-btn-submit` → both call doSubmit() synchronously in the same tick → TWO POST /Submit/Post requests → TWO duplicate submission rows per submit (verified on :5114: wellness/down-under/rsvp each created 2 submissionIds from one click; a payment form would double-charge). FIX = a re-entrancy guard in the renderer (`submitInFlight`): set right before the XHR POST and cleared on `onloadend`, so the second synchronous doSubmit() bails. Does NOT block the legitimate review→confirm sequence (the review path returns before the flag is set) nor a later "Submit another". Renderer JS only (src/renderer/index.ts → megaform-renderer.js); AssetVersion→20260705-B371. Verified: one click → exactly ONE POST, thank-you pane intact, across both the native (`data-mf-native-page`) and template (`data-step` au/bg/ey/fi) step mechanisms. Carries v1.7.85.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.85 (20260705) — 🔧 Carries the v1.7.84 premium-form interaction fixes into the shipped premium TEMPLATES: the per-template customCss copies of `.mf-premium-native-mode .mf-form-actions{display:none}` and `.mfp-&lt;slug&gt; .mf-form-actions{display:none}` (down-under, euro-youth, americana-journey, bulgaria) now carry `:not(.mf-postsubmit-actions):not(.mf-review-actions)` so the post-submit thank-you and review action buttons show on forms created from those templates (the canonical megaform.css rule alone is overridden by these per-template copies). No DLL/JS/CSS change vs 1.7.84 (AssetVersion stays B370); template wwwroot content only. Carries v1.7.84.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.84 (20260705) — 🔧 3 premium-form interaction fixes (date picker, review summary, thank-you pane). (1) DATE PICKER popup was CLIPPED at the premium card's rounded edge — the template's `.mfp{overflow:hidden!important}` (specificity ~0,5,0) beat the `.mf-has-date-popover` overflow-lift (0,3,0). The renderer now lifts `overflow:visible` INLINE (!important, beats any stylesheet rule) on the field's ancestors while a picker is open, restoring it on close (driven by a MutationObserver on `.is-open`; no re-parenting, outside-click intact). Also the calendar ICON collapsed to mid-field (over the placeholder) because premium templates style `.mf-input` at very high specificity, flipping the `.mf-cal-trigger` to display:block; the icon is now pinned ABSOLUTELY to the right of the (relative) trigger so it's correct whether the trigger is flex or block. (2) REVIEW SUMMARY values were blank on euro-youth/bulgaria/festa — `updatePremiumSummary` only matched the `data-au-summary` static-slot prefix, so other templates' slots never filled; it now matches every prefix (au/ey/bg/fi) + the Core `data-mf-summary-key`, so existing forms fill their review with the user's actual entries. (3) THANK-YOU / REVIEW pane action buttons were invisible on every premium form: `.mf-premium-native-mode .mf-form-actions{display:none}` (added to hide the duplicate footer) also hid the post-submit `.mf-postsubmit-actions` and `.mf-review-actions`; now scoped with `:not(.mf-postsubmit-actions):not(.mf-review-actions)`. Canonical `Assets/css/megaform.css` + 3 wwwroot copies synced. AssetVersion→20260705-B370. Carries v1.7.83.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.83 (20260705) — 🔧 FIX premium multi-step custom-shell forms (e.g. form 7 "Classic Car Show") painting a BROKEN first frame for ~2.5s: an EMPTY body (no active-step fields) plus a stray generic "Submit/Gửi" button below the shell card, then snapping correct after JS hydrate. Root cause = SSR/client parity gap: the premium shell's authored CSS hides every `.mfp-page` and reveals only `.mfp-page.is-active`, but this template does NOT bake `is-active` on step 0 (unlike americana-journey), and the SSR wrapper lacked `mf-premium-native-mode` — both are applied only client-side on hydrate. So at first paint every step was `display:none` (empty body) and the generic `.mf-form-actions` (which the client hides via `.mf-premium-native-mode .mf-form-actions{display:none}`) stayed visible. FIX (SSR-only, gated to premium-native multi-step custom HTML via the durable `mfp-native-generated`/`data-mf-native-page` markers): (1) Core `FormHtmlRenderer.RenderCustomHtml` now injects `is-active` onto the FIRST `data-mf-native-page` step — idempotent (skips templates that already bake it) and inert for non-premium custom HTML — so ALL platforms show step 1 at SSR; (2) the Oqtane module SSR (Index.razor) and the anon render page (RenderPage.cs) now add `mf-custom-html-mode mf-premium-native-mode mf-has-multistep-shell` to the wrapper for these forms, so the existing CSS hides the generic action bar at first paint. Standard forms, single-page custom shells, and non-premium custom shells are untouched (gated). Server-DLL/SSR-only fix; AssetVersion unchanged (B369). Verified on :5113: form 7 first paint now shows step 1 + fields and no stray Submit button. Carries v1.7.82.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.82 (20260705) — ✨ "Hide form header" toggle surfaced in ⚙ Settings → Theme &amp; Layout. The per-form Hide-Form-Header option (suppresses the title + description block, `settings.hideHeader`) was previously only reachable in the full builder; it is now a checkbox in the Settings popup's Layout section, so admins can toggle it without opening the builder. Persisted to the FORM via the existing partial-patch Form/SaveTheme endpoint (new optional `HideHeader` field — leaves theme/css/inherit untouched; added to all 3 platform controllers Oqtane/Web/DNN for parity), read back through getFormThemeLayout, and applied by the renderer/SSR as `.mf-hide-header`. Verified end-to-end on :5113: toggle → Save → reload → the header is hidden and the checkbox reads back checked. SaveTheme stays admin-gated ([Authorize(Policy=EditModule)] on Oqtane). AssetVersion→20260705-B369. Carries v1.7.81.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.81 (20260705) — ✨ Typography &amp; Corner-radius controls in ⚙ Settings + 2 platform fixes. (1) NEW form-level Typography (Body font · Heading font · Base text size · Line height) and Corner-radius (Sharp/Rounded/Soft/Pill preset + Custom slider) controls in ⚙ Settings → Theme &amp; Layout, so all form styling lives in one popup rather than only in the Theme Designer. Wired to the SAME --mf-* vars megaform.css actually consumes — body→--mf-font-family, heading→--mf-title-font-family, base→--mf-font-size-base, line-height→--mf-line-height (stored UNITLESS — a dedicated row, since the px sliderRow/mfReadPx would truncate 1.5→1), radius→--mf-form-radius — and they round-trip through the same setLayoutVar → SaveModuleStyle → GetModuleStyle (the 1.7.76 JsonElement read-back) path with no server change. (2) 🔧 FIX 404 on builder/theme-designer i18n on Oqtane (/DesktopModules/MegaForm/Assets/js/builder/i18n/&lt;loc&gt;.json): resolveI18nBase() defaulted to the DNN static path whenever the Oqtane markers (window.Oqtane / [data-platform=oqtane]) had not booted yet — it now falls back to the Oqtane API base (/api/MegaForm/ → /api/MegaForm/i18n/Get, a real 200 route) unless there is POSITIVE DNN evidence, so genuine DNN is unaffected. (3) 🔧 FIX 400 on /api/MegaFormSubmit/Post (note the missing slash): the ACTIVE renderer (src/renderer/index.ts — the dead src/renderer/megaform-renderer.ts the earlier note named is not shipped) now normalizes config.apiBaseUrl to always end with '/' at the init chokepoint, so a caller passing '/api/MegaForm' (platform-host getApiBase returns the base WITHOUT a trailing slash) no longer collapses 'Submit/Post'/'Draft/Save' into a bad route. AssetVersion→20260705-B368. Carries v1.7.80.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.80 (20260705) — 💅 UX: the ⚙ Settings popup now presents its sections (Module form · Theme &amp; Layout · Current Form settings) as TABS instead of stacked accordions. With accordions, expanding a section (esp. Theme &amp; Layout with 16 preset tiles + the editable palettes) grew the dialog until the Save button scrolled out of view — worst in inline mode where the dialog has no fixed height. Tabs show ONE section at a time inside a bounded, internally-scrolling pane (max ~58vh), so the dialog stays compact and "Save module settings" is always reachable. Each existing section builder is reused (its title + content are lifted out of the accordion chrome into a tab pane); the active tab is remembered across re-renders. Verified in-browser: 3 tabs, switching works, the tall Theme tab scrolls inside its pane, and Save stays in the viewport on every tab. AssetVersion→20260705-B367. Carries v1.7.79.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.79 (20260705) — 🔧 FIX phantom DOUBLE border at the top/edge of premium/custom-shell form cards. CustomShellCompatibilityCssService put `border:1px solid transparent` on `.mfp[class*=mfp-]>.mfp-container` — a ~0.67px reserved band between the container edge and the inner `.mfp-card`'s own border. Because the container and the stripped `.mfp`/`.mf-form` shell above it are transparent, that band reveals the host page background right beside the card border → on a dark-backgrounded host (e.g. the Oqtane home content pane) it reads as a thin second line = a phantom double border. The container needs no border of its own (the card has one), so it is now `border:0` and the card sits flush. Verified in-browser: the 0.67px container→card gap goes 0.67px → 0. Core/render-only fix; AssetVersion unchanged (B366, inline CSS). Carries v1.7.78.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.78 (20260705) — 🔧 FIX admin-panel FOUC (raw-HTML flash on load) for Submissions / My Inbox / Languages / Workflow-inbox. Their stylesheets (megaform-admin-shell.css + the per-surface *-ts.css) are declared as Oqtane component Resources, which the Interactive host injects via JS interop ~2.5s AFTER hydration — so those panels first painted as UNSTYLED raw HTML, then snapped into place. The B357 fix only covered the Dashboard panel. Index.razor now emits the correct render-blocking &lt;link&gt; set for the ACTIVE admin surface inside the (pre)rendered SSR markup, so the browser has the CSS before first paint (verified: the 4 admin CSS now appear in the initial server HTML for ?mfpanel=submissions, not just after hydrate). Public form path emits none. Client-DLL/SSR-only fix; AssetVersion unchanged (B366). Carries v1.7.77.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.77 (20260705) — ✨ NEW per-preset editable colour palette in the ⚙ Settings → Theme &amp; Layout → Theme preset section. Each preset tile now has a ▾ caret that drops down an editable palette of the four semantic colours it is built from — Primary, Text, Surface, Accent — each with a native colour picker AND a typed hex field (kept in sync). Editing a colour re-applies the full --mf-* palette to the form, selects that preset, and marks it dirty; the Save button persists it (module style) and the render consumes it. A "Reset to default" restores the preset's shipped colours. Verified end-to-end: edit Ocean Primary → #e11d48 → Save → submit button renders rgb(225,29,72) → reopen shows the edited hex. AssetVersion→20260705-B366. Carries v1.7.76.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.76 (20260705) — 🔧 FIX Theme &amp; Layout settings (Field spacing / preset / max-width) appeared to never save — the ⚙ settings popup's slider always showed the 20px default on reopen and admins thought nothing persisted. Root cause: GET ModuleConfig/ModuleStyle returned a raw Newtonsoft JObject, but Oqtane serializes controller responses with System.Text.Json, which cannot serialize a Newtonsoft JObject and emitted garbage (themeCssOverrides → [[[]]]) — so the client read every var as unset and the slider fell back to its default. The save DID persist (DB correct) and the public render DID apply the value (verified: 15px stored → 15px actual field gap); only the popup's read-back was broken. GetModuleStyle now returns a System.Text.Json JsonElement (both the stored and seed-from-form paths). Oqtane-only (Web/DNN use Newtonsoft output). Server-DLL-only fix; AssetVersion unchanged (B365). Carries v1.7.75.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.75 (20260705) — 🔧 FIX SEC-B1 regression: adding [ValidateAntiForgeryToken] to Oqtane SaveModuleStyle in v1.7.74 made the module-style Save return 400 when the ⚙ settings popup opened on a page that loads ONLY megaform-settings-popup.js (a rendered form in edit mode) — that bundle did not install the same-origin antiforgery header chokepoint, so its fetch never carried X-XSRF-TOKEN-HEADER. The settings-popup entry now imports shared/antiforgery so the chokepoint self-installs and SaveStyle/SaveModuleStyle carry the token. AssetVersion→20260705-B365 (busts the cached settings-popup bundle). Carries v1.7.74.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.74 (20260705) — 🔒 SECURITY + ⚡ PERF (Sprint 0+1 remediation, commit e589ab6). SECURITY: (SEC-B1) Oqtane SaveModuleStyle now carries [ValidateAntiForgeryToken] (was CSRF-exposed under the class-level [IgnoreAntiforgeryToken]; client already sends the token via the shared antiforgery chokepoint). (SEC-B2) payment amount enforcement was effectively a NO-OP because the unified payment widget never sent formId, so the server always fail-opened to the client "amount" — the widget now stamps data-mf-form-id and sends it in the Stripe/PayPal create bodies, and PaymentController.ResolveServerAmount now FAILS CLOSED when the form context is missing (deploy the plugin + server together; a stale plugin omits formId and is rejected). (SEC-M) WebhookService now routes user-configured webhook URLs through SsrfGuard (previously only the workflow WebhookNodeExecutor did). PERF: (PERF-A1) content-addressed memoization of RenderModelResolver.ResolveSchemaJson — the heaviest render step (JObject parse + DeepClone + ToString of ~165 KB schemas, run 5-6x per public form view) — plus a 30s TTL cache for the per-render license.lic disk read; (PERF-C1) DNN RazorWidget proxy uses one shared HttpClient + per-call CancellationTokenSource instead of 6 per-call clients (socket exhaustion); (PERF-C2) captcha verification uses a shared static HttpClient with a 10s timeout on the public submit path; (OPS-1) per-IP flood rate limiter on the standalone Web host. AssetVersion→20260705-B364 (payment plugin recompiled). Carries v1.7.73.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.73 (20260704) — 🔒 SECURITY (2 more flow-safe hardenings from the Mythos re-audit) + AssetVersion→20260704-B363. (P1-2/P1-11) The Oqtane module style / ModuleConfig / image-upload popup endpoints (SaveStyle, SaveModuleStyle, GetModuleStyle, GetModuleConfig, SaveModuleConfig, Upload/Image, Upload/List) gated on CanUseAdminPopup() which only checked IsAuthenticated — so ANY logged-in user (incl. a low-privilege registered user) could POST an arbitrary victim's moduleId (a cross-module IDOR whose SaveModuleStyle write is also a stored-XSS vector). CanUseAdminPopup now requires the site Admin or Host role. (Deliberately NOT the stricter per-target-module EditModule policy: the cross-platform settings popup often calls these WITHOUT the alias prefix so AuthEntityId can't resolve the module — an EditModule/AuthEntityId check would 403 that legitimate path; role-gating closes the "any authenticated user" hole without breaking it. Per-module ownership remains a follow-up.) (P2-8) The builder inline-edit preview posted the form's full schema/settings to window.parent using a target origin derived from document.referrer, which a page that cross-embeds the builder preview could poison to receive it — now always posts to the same-origin parent (never document.referrer), and the builder receiver validates event.origin === location.origin. Server + JS bundles (megaform-renderer.js + megaform-builder.js) rebuilt. Carries v1.7.72.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.72 (20260703) — 🔒 SECURITY (P1/P2/P3 flow-safe pass) + field-spacing cache-bust + AssetVersion→20260703-B360. SECURITY (surgical, form build/render/submit/payment flows unaffected — see Docs/SECURITY_P1_P2_P3_REMEDIATION_2026-07-03.md): (P0-8, NEW) Workflow Webhook SSRF — a PUBLIC form submission could steer the server's outbound webhook at cloud metadata / internal hosts via {{field.*}} URL tokens; new MegaForm.Core SsrfGuard rejects non-http(s) + loopback/private/link-local/CGNAT/metadata (169.254.169.254) targets (DNS resolved up-front so rebinding is caught), with an on-prem opt-out env MEGAFORM_ALLOW_PRIVATE_WEBHOOKS=1. (P0-9, NEW) MegaForm.AspNetCore.Component hardcoded JWT key + disabled issuer/audience validation → now env-first (MEGAFORM_JWT_KEY) and validates issuer/audience when configured, mirroring the Web host. (P1-3) Web Local-AI kimi CLI spawn restricted to Admin/Host (KB answers stay open to any authed user). (P1-4/5/6) the option-source / DatabaseInsert / lifecycle-hook SQL guards (all run on public-facing paths) were substring-matched ("INSERT " with a trailing space) — hardened to word-boundary + reject statement-stacking + reject comment obfuscation, so INSERT\tINTO / "…;UPDATE…" bypasses are closed while single legit statements still run; stored-proc option names restricted to a plain identifier. (P1-8) Files/Download path traversal — replaced the bypassable path.Replace("..","") with canonical Path.GetFullPath containment (Oqtane + DNN). (P2-1) CORS lockable to MEGAFORM_CORS_ORIGINS (Web + AspNetCore.Component); (P2-2) Component auth cookie Secure outside Development; (P2-4) X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff on private downloads. DEFERRED (would break the workflow, documented not applied): P0-1 unauth RazorWidget DML + P0-2 payment amount (need server-side schema/price resolution), P1-1/P1-2 class-level antiforgery removal (needs the JS fetch layer to send a token first), P1-7 content-token SSR encoding (premium templates embed HTML in tokens), P3 config defaults (flipping TrustServerCertificate breaks local SQL). FIELD-SPACING: the v1.7.71 rebuilt megaform-settings-popup.js bundle now cache-busts for all browsers (AssetVersion bumped B359→B360) so the "Field spacing" slider reflects the saved --mf-field-gap without a manual hard-refresh. Carries v1.7.71/70/69/68.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.71 (20260703) — FIX Settings → "Field spacing" slider appeared to not save (always reverted to 20px). The value DID persist and DID apply to the rendered form (MegaForm:ModuleStyleJson stored --mf-field-gap and the render emitted it) — but the module's megaform-settings-popup.js bundle in wwwroot was STALE (never rebuilt by `npm run build`, which omits the settings-popup entry), so the deployed slider re-read the wrong source on reopen and showed the 20px default. Rebuilt megaform-settings-popup.js from current source (loadFormTheme awaits getModuleStyle — the module-owned style — before building the slider) so the slider now reflects the saved value. No C# change; carries the v1.7.70 Rating fix + v1.7.69 security + v1.7.68 KB eager-seed. (NOTE for maintainers: add build:settings-popup to the npm `build` script so this bundle stops going stale.)
      PREVIOUS v1.7.70 (20260703) — FIX Rating widget rendered VERTICALLY on server-rendered forms. FormHtmlRenderer emitted the star spans (&lt;span class="mf-star"&gt;) as DIRECT children of .mf-rating, which is display:grid — so each star fell on its own grid row (stars stacked top-to-bottom). The client renderer (inputs.ts) wraps them in the flex .mf-rating-items; the SSR path did not — an SSR/client parity gap. FormHtmlRenderer now emits the same structure (.mf-rating--star &gt; .mf-rating-items &gt; button.mf-rating-item.mf-star with .mf-rating-on/off), so the stars lay out horizontally and hydrate/style consistently. Added a defensive CSS net (.mf-rating:has(&gt; .mf-star)) for any legacy bare-star markup. Server-DLL fix; note: the module Settings pane already exposes vertical row spacing as "Field spacing" (var --mf-field-gap) under Theme &amp; Layout. Carries v1.7.69 security. Carries v1.7.68 KB eager-seed.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.69 (20260703) — 🔒 SECURITY (P0 remediation, flow-safe). Fixes for the Mythos audit's Critical findings, made surgically so the form build/render/submit/payment flows are unaffected: (P0-1) the Razor-widget Action SQL path (EditableList/MasterDetailList) now runs client SQL through a new destructive-SQL guard (MegaForm.Core RazorActionSqlGuard) — SELECT/INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE still pass so the widget Add/Edit/Delete buttons keep working, but DROP/ALTER/EXEC/xp_/sp_/statement-stacking/comments are rejected, closing the unauthenticated "DROP TABLE" hole. (P0-4) the Oqtane Local-AI chat/completions endpoint (builder assistant, can spawn the env-gated kimi CLI) is tightened from any-authenticated-user to Admin/Host only. (P0-3) the Web Local-AI chat/completions endpoint drops [AllowAnonymous] → [Authorize]. (P0-6) ModuleCssComposer now neutralises the "&lt;/" token in authored customCss/moduleCssOverride so a payload can't break out of the &lt;style&gt; block (stored XSS); raw CustomHtml is intentionally left as-is (admin-authored premium-shell feature). (P0-7, DNN) the public AppEndpoint SQL guard now rejects any DML/DDL keyword anywhere (word-boundary), closing the "WITH cte … DELETE" CTE-hidden-write bypass. (P0-5, Web) the JWT signing key + issuer/audience are read from environment variables first and the committed production key was rotated to a placeholder (set MEGAFORM_JWT_KEY on the host). (P0-2) payment amount tampering is documented in-code as needing a coordinated widget+schema change (server-side price resolution) and is NOT auto-fixed, to avoid breaking variable-amount forms. Server/Core/Web/DNN all compile clean. Carries v1.7.68.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.68 (20260703) — ⭐FIX empty AI Knowledge Base on fresh NuGet installs (MF_AI_Knowledge = 0 rows → AI premium-edit had no KB context). Root cause was NOT the migration seed SQL: on Oqtane MegaFormManager.Install() builds the schema from the EF MODEL (GenerateCreateScript) and SeedMigrationHistory() marks EVERY migration applied WITHOUT ever running its Up() — so the template-guide seed in migrations 01.06.35/36/37 is dead code here and never executed. The only runtime seed path is the LAZY JSON seeder (OqtaneKbSeederHostedService.SeedEntries, embedded ai-knowledge-seed.json) which fires on the first authenticated KB read — so a fresh install with no AI use sits at 0 rows. Fix: (1) MegaFormManager.Install now EAGERLY seeds the KB (entries + templates + rules) right after creating the schema, in the install request scope where the tenant connection is resolved — idempotent (empty-check) and defensive (a seed hiccup never fails the module install; the lazy first-read seed remains as fallback). (2) Added the 3 recent premium template_guide entries (americana-journey, event-registration-rsvp, wellness-patient-intake) that migration 37 introduced but that never seeded on Oqtane (their Up() is dead code) so the AI premium-edit assistant gets their .guide.md design context — the JSON now seeds 321 KB rows (24→27 template_guides; the other premium templates already ship as form_template entries and can't hold a second row per slug). Removed the useless migration 01.06.38 (Up() never runs on Oqtane). Verified on the clean SQL Express :5100 site: MF_AI_Knowledge goes 0 → 321 on upgrade. Server-DLL-only change (no wwwroot/JS churn); AssetVersion unchanged. Carries v1.7.66.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.66 (20260703) — Two Blazor enhanced-nav (SPA) fixes: (1) Builder rendered BLANK when navigating in-tab to a different builder (?mfpanel=builder&amp;formId=N) — the loader guard was a GLOBAL flag that stuck true across SPA nav; now per-root (root.dataset.mfBooted) + MegaFormBuilder.reInit wired to re-boot a freshly-mounted empty root. (2) Two forms overlapped when switching forms in-tab — the renderer now drops any stale sibling .mf-form-wrapper in the module container before render (1 module = 1 form). AssetVersion→20260703-B359. &#10;PREVIOUS v1.7.65 (20260703) — Builder boot: dedupe the duplicate Form/Get. The builder has two boot paths (panels.ts initBuilder + dom.ts bootBuilderDom) that BOTH fetched the same Form/Get on open — on a real form that is 2× ~3s identical requests. A shared in-flight promise cache (boot-fetch-dedup.ts) keyed by formId now serves one request to both paths, cutting ~3s off builder open. Perf note: the remaining builder slowness is HTTP/1.1 connection queueing (118 resources) — needs HTTP/2 (requires TLS) — plus eager widget-plugin registration (~2.4MB JS) that should lazy-load on drag; these are follow-ups. AssetVersion→20260703-B358.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.64 (20260703) — Premium template-guide KB seed completeness: added the AI premium-edit KB seed rows for americana-journey + the two new templates event-registration-rsvp and wellness-patient-intake (their .facts.json/.guide.md already shipped, but no MF_AI_Knowledge row existed, so the AI assistant lacked per-template context). Added to the canonical Seed/ai-knowledge-template-guides.sql + a new idempotent migration 01.06.37 (MERGE / INSERT-WHERE-NOT-EXISTS, safe on existing DBs). Package now passes verify-package-complete for all 7 shipped premium templates. Carries the dashboard FOUC fix + 2 new templates + first-paint anti-jank work.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.63 (20260703) — Dashboard FOUC fix: the admin/dashboard shell CSS (megaform-admin-shell.css) was only delivered via the async JS boot &lt;link&gt;, which on the Interactive host is eval'd ~2.5s into boot — so ?mfpanel=dashboard painted UNSTYLED then snapped into place (flicker). It is now emitted as a render-blocking &lt;link&gt; inside the prerendered panel markup so the browser has the shell CSS before the dashboard paints; the JS boot still re-injects it for SPA panel nav (idempotent). AssetVersion→20260703-B357. Carries the two new premium templates + first-paint anti-jank work.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.62 (20260703) — Two new premium templates shipped: "Event Registration &amp; RSVP" (event-registration-rsvp) and "Wellness &amp; Patient Intake" (wellness-patient-intake) added to wwwroot/Modules/MegaForm/Templates so a clean NuGet install seeds them into the gallery like the other premium starters. Fixed an invalid `type:"Input"` on their name/text fields → `Text` (Input is not a recognized MegaForm field type, so those fields fell through to the default renderer). Carries the v1.7.60/61 first-paint anti-jank work (auFade cloak + premium-native multistep gap:0).
      PREVIOUS v1.7.61 (20260703) — Premium-native top-gap jump fix: the generic multi-step shell the renderer wraps around a custom form is `display:flex;gap:20px` between its header/body/footer. Premium shells (australia/americana/…) render their OWN stepper + Back/Next/Submit so that header/footer are hidden, but the flex gap still reserved ~20px above AND below the card — and because the shell is built by JS AFTER the SSR card has painted, those 40px land LATE, dropping the card ~20px and growing the block ~40px = a visible top-padding "giật". An americana-only rule already zeroed this; now a general `.mf-premium-native-mode.mf-has-multistep-shell .mf-multistep-frame{gap:0}` covers every premium template (down-under included). AssetVersion→20260703-B356. Carries v1.7.60.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.60 (20260702) — First-paint anti-jank cloak (SSR-baked, no re-trigger): the real cause of the premium-form "giật" is the per-step entrance keyframe (auFade/amFade: opacity 0→1 + translateY 6px) which — because .au-page.is-active + the animation live in the SSR template CSS — PLAYS AT SERVER FIRST PAINT (~250ms), before the schema returns. v1.7.59 cloaked only after JS ran (too late) and used animation:none, which restarted the entrance the moment the class lifted. Now the SSR wrapper ships with .mf-booting baked in (Index.razor + /render), .mf-booting pushes one-shot entrances to their final frame via a large negative animation-delay (no motion, no 0%-flash, animation-name stays detectable), and the renderer PINS the on-screen step's entrance off before lifting the class one frame after hydrate — so it never replays. Step-change animations during real navigation are untouched; spinners keep spinning. AssetVersion→20260702-B355. Carries v1.7.58.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.59 (20260702) — First-paint anti-jank cloak: on Oqtane Interactive the schema is fetched ~250ms after first paint, so the renderer hydrates the form late and premium shells run their per-step entrance animation (auFade/amFade: opacity 0→1 + translateY(6px)) plus a width settle transition AFTER the page has painted — reading as a visible fade+slide "giật", not an effect. The renderer now cloaks the wrapper with .mf-booting (animation:none + transition:none) around the whole synchronous hydrate and lifts it on the next frame, so the first step lands in its final position instantly while real step-change animations still play during navigation. AssetVersion→20260702-B354. Carries v1.7.58.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.58 (20260702) — Custom-shell SSR bind-only completion: the public renderer now detects data-mf-ssr customHtml shells and hydrates bind-only (conditional logic, managed scripts, native Back/Next/Submit) instead of calling renderCustomHtml()/innerHTML after paint. Combined with v1.7.57 Row de-dup, this prevents both the 4-column→2-column snap and the later custom shell repaint on FormId 4. AssetVersion→20260702-B353. Carries v1.7.57.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.57 (20260702) — Row SSR first-paint parity: FormHtmlRenderer collapses exact duplicate Row columns caused by legacy payloads carrying both columns and Columns, so first/last name paints as 2 columns from SSR instead of snapping back after JS hydrate. Carries v1.7.56.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.56 (20260702) — Custom-shell header first-paint parity: FormHtmlRenderer now receives the persisted form title/description/submit text from Oqtane host and /render, so {{form:title}} and {{form:description}} are filled in SSR instead of appearing later when JS hydrates. Prevents header-on forms from pushing fields down after paint. AssetVersion→20260702-B352. Carries v1.7.55.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.55 (20260702) — Custom-shell Hide Form Header first-paint coverage: core megaform.css now also collapses mfp-card-header/default/header/title/desc selectors under mf-hide-header, so Custom HTML Active forms do not show the template header/title during first paint. AssetVersion→20260702-B351. Carries v1.7.54.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.54 (20260702) — Hide Form Header first-paint fix: when settings.hideHeader is true, Oqtane SSR and /api/MegaForm/render no longer emit the standard form header/title markup, renderer fallback skips header creation too, and megaform.css carries an early mf-hide-header collapse rule. Prevents late header/title appearance from shifting the form after paint. AssetVersion→20260702-B350. Carries v1.7.53.
    PREVIOUS v1.7.53 (20260702) — Oqtane Interactive one-pass SSR hydration: renderer skips duplicate init once SSR DOM is hydrated, full SSR shells bypass buildSkeleton entirely, and the Oqtane boot script locks per container/form before schema fetch so the form prepares once and then only JS-binds navigation/validation/submit. AssetVersion→20260702-B349. Carries v1.7.52.
    PREVIOUS v1.7.52 (20260702) — Deploy-correct hidden-root keepalive: synced the Oqtane packaged wwwroot megaform.css source with the direct-body display:none keepalive rule, so the package actually ships the black/blank-frame fix. AssetVersion→20260702-B348. Carries v1.7.51.
    PREVIOUS v1.7.51 (20260702) — Oqtane Interactive hidden-root keepalive: megaform.css now force-displays the direct body prerender wrapper only when it contains MegaForm SSR, preventing Oqtane's temporary display:none boot wrapper from producing a black/blank frame before the live tree appears. AssetVersion→20260702-B347. Carries v1.7.50.
    PREVIOUS v1.7.50 (20260702) — SSR snapshot restore hardening: stores first-paint form HTML under exact module key plus site/form and form-only fallback keys, so the Oqtane Interactive circuit can restore _ssrFieldsHtml during its loading pass even when PageId/ModuleId state differs from prerender. Closes the remaining post-negotiate blank window before bind-only hydration. AssetVersion→20260702-B346. Carries v1.7.49.
    PREVIOUS v1.7.49 (20260702) — SSR multi-step anti-blank guard for Oqtane Interactive: suppresses the transient loading render while the interactive circuit is rebuilding SSR state, preserving the prerendered server form DOM until _ssrFieldsHtml is ready. Prevents the short black/blank swap seen between SSR markup and final hydrated form. AssetVersion→20260702-B345. Carries v1.7.48.
    PREVIOUS v1.7.48 (20260702) — SSR multi-step first paint: standard multi-step forms now render server-side with .mf-page wrappers, stepper, actions, and a full Oqtane shell so the Interactive host does not tear SSR into a skeleton while waiting for the Blazor circuit. Renderer detects data-mf-ssr-multistep and hydrates bind-only instead of rebuilding pages/stepper. AssetVersion→20260702-B344. Carries v1.7.47.
    PREVIOUS v1.7.47 (20260702) — 🔒 SECURITY (unauth remediation) + FOUC root-cause fix. (1) P0-1 kimi local-AI RCE (Oqtane MegaFormLocalAiController): the /api/MegaFormAi/chat/completions fallback shelled out to a local `kimi` CLI with the user query STRING-INTERPOLATED into the args and NO env gate → unauth argument injection / RCE. Now: [Authorize] on the endpoint + opt-in env gate MEGAFORM_ALLOW_LOCAL_AI_CLI=1 + ProcessStartInfo.ArgumentList (argv array, no shell string) — mirrors the already-safe Web variant. (2) P0-2 i18n write→stored-XSS (Oqtane MegaFormController.UpsertI18nLocale, routes i18n/create·save·import): was the only write path in the controller WITHOUT [Authorize] → anyone could write attacker JSON to a locale file rendered in the builder. Added [Authorize(Policy=EditModule)] + reject overwriting the `index` manifest. (3) P0-5 SavePrintSettings (Web PrintController): unauthenticated → anyone could rewrite a form's print header/footer HTML (stored XSS). Added [Authorize(Roles=Administrator)]. (4) AiKnowledgeController.SeedViewModes: was the lone KB mutator missing the `if(!IsAdmin) return Forbid();` guard → anon DB write; added it. (5) ⭐FOUC/double-render fix: FormHtmlRenderer.RenderFieldsBody now de-dupes fields by key before SSR (matching the client's byKey hydrate). A form whose stored schema had every field duplicated painted 36 field-groups for 18 fields → a visible "double-then-collapse" flash + 2x payload. NOTE: two unauthenticated surfaces remain FLAGGED for a design fix (server-side validation, not a bare [Authorize]): RazorWidget/Action (arbitrary SQL, but invoked by anonymous form runtime) and PaymentController stripe/paypal (merchant-credential endpoints legitimately hit by anonymous payers). AssetVersion unchanged (server-only). Carries v1.7.46.
    PREVIOUS v1.7.46 (20260702) — (1) FIX duplicate footer buttons on premium-native shells (euro-youth/intake/down-under/festa/bulgaria): the shell renders its own Back/Next/Submit AND the generic renderer injected .mf-form-actions → two "Next"/"Submit" buttons. Now hidden deterministically from first paint via CSS keyed on the always-set .mf-premium-native-mode wrapper class (also removes the generic-actions flash). (2) Inspector colour rows get a curated COLOUR PALETTE popover (swatch grid + recent + native custom picker) instead of just the OS picker. AssetVersion→20260702-B343. Carries v1.7.45.
    PREVIOUS v1.7.45 (20260702) — Theme Designer (builder Design tab): (1) removed the unfinished/unused LEFT-rail Elements + Colors tabs (only Presets remains). (2) Typography font dropdowns now have a clearly visible border + chevron (was near-invisible #e2e8f0 and could be overridden by the host Bootstrap .form-control). (3) The CSS element picker moved from the (removed) left Colors tab to the RIGHT-rail Inspector sub-tab and was FIXED to actually work: it silently did nothing because (a) the pick-result event was dispatched non-bubbling on document but the panel listens on window, and (b) the iframe applied edits as plain inline style which premium template CSS (!important) overrode. Now: Pick element → the picked element's CSS lists on the right with per-property inputs + colour swatches, and edits apply live to the preview (inline !important). AssetVersion→20260702-B342. Carries all v1.7.44 fixes.
    PREVIOUS v1.7.40 (20260701) — ⭐CRITICAL DEPLOY FIX: the Oqtane ModuleDefinition.Version was frozen at "1.7.15" across every release, so Oqtane treated each new package as "already installed" and NEVER replaced the module DLLs on upgrade (only wwwroot updated) — every C# fix since 1.7.15 silently failed to deploy on existing sites. Bumped ModuleDefinition.Version to 1.7.40 (+ ReleaseVersions) so upgrades actually swap the DLLs. This finally deploys the v1.7.38 i18n Save fix + v1.7.39 template-seed and dashboard bloat-guard on upgraded sites. (1) FIX empty Business Starters / Template Gallery on a CLEAN install: the premium starter templates were only read from App_Data/MegaForm/Templates, which the NuGet never populated → BuilderTemplateCatalogService now SEEDS App_Data from the shipped wwwroot/Modules/MegaForm/Templates copy on first run (5 premium templates now ship in the package). (2) FIX "Dashboard shows no forms" on a fresh site: an AI form with a QRCode field holding a 1.5MB base64 logo produced a 3MB schema; rendering it inline as a Blazor MarkupString threw "Unexpected end of input" in insertMarkup and ABORTED the whole page render, so the dashboard's form-list load never ran. Added a ~700KB size guard on the inline schema preload + SSR fields body — oversized forms fall back to the client fetch/render instead of crashing. Carries v1.7.38 i18n Save fix.
    PREVIOUS v1.7.38 (20260701) — ⭐FIX Language Manager "Save" not persisting: the i18n Get endpoint read js/bundles/i18n (shipped defaults) BEFORE js/builder/i18n (author overrides written by i18n/save). Since the package ships every locale in bundles/i18n, saved/AI-translated strings were shadowed → "Save" appeared to do nothing on reload. GetI18nLocale now reads builder/i18n (overrides) first. AssetVersion unchanged (server-side fix). Carries v1.7.37 Content-Slider editor fix.
    PREVIOUS v1.7.37 (20260701) — ⭐FIX Content Slider editor regression: the packaged wwwroot shipped a STALE content-slider widget plugin (js/plugins/megaform-widget-content-slider.js, old 20KB from 06-17) instead of the 06-28 redesign (42KB, Overlay/Card/Cards templates + Ken Burns + drag-follow) → installing overwrote the live plugin with the old one → the rich "Open Slider Designer" modal was missing. Rebuilt the plugin from source (tsc plugins/tsconfig) and synced to the package wwwroot. AssetVersion→20260701-B341. Carries v1.7.36 Import-JSON fix.
    PREVIOUS v1.7.36 (20260701) — ⭐FIX Wizard Import-JSON: (1) the DEPLOYED default templates put customHtml/customCss at the TOP LEVEL (not inside settings) → wizardTemplateFromJson now merges top-level custom* into settings so premium templates import WITH their shell (was silently downgraded to a plain standard form). (2) Import was silent (a valid file only changed the off-screen name field → felt like nothing happened) → now shows a toast "Imported \"…\" — N fields loaded", and JSON/parse errors surface as toasts instead of alert(). +4 wiz.import_* keys (de/vi). AssetVersion→20260701-B340. Carries v1.7.35 Wizard i18n.
    PREVIOUS v1.7.35 (20260701) — ⭐Form Wizard i18n: the wizard shell, step-nav, Setup step and Template-Gallery/Import-JSON modal are now keyed under wiz.* (46 keys) with German + Vietnamese translations shipped and English placeholders for the rest (fill via the in-product "Translate (AI)" tool). I18N_CACHE_VERSION bumped so stale locale caches drop. AssetVersion→20260701-B339. Carries v1.7.34.
    PREVIOUS v1.7.34 (20260701) — ⭐NEW option-icon PALETTE (pick emoji + MegaForm icon catalog for Chips/Cards option icons, no more raw typing) + FIX euro-youth stray 1px card border above the stepper (CustomShellCompatibilityCssService NOINNER now recognizes the nested .ey-card so the transparent outer .mfp stays borderless) + Form Wizard entry paths: a Template Gallery browse modal (category + search + preview) and Import-JSON, parallel to starting from scratch. Complete language packs (38 locales). AssetVersion→20260701-B338.
    PREVIOUS v1.7.33 (20260626) — ⭐FIX AI multi-step + AI form polish: (1) AI multi-step forms always showed an EMPTY first page — a page-break Section on the FIRST field made calculatePages() emit an empty leading page; it now only starts a new page when the current page has content (leading/consecutive page breaks no longer create blank pages). (2) Step labels are now derived from the actual page structure (fieldPages) — the leading section names step 1 correctly instead of a generic off-by-one "Step 1". (3) Multi-step (standard) forms dropped the gray --mf-page-bg wrapper frame ("card thừa bên ngoài") via .mf-form-wrapper:has(.mf-steps) so the white card sits on the page, consistent with the frameless single-page AI forms. (4) AI pure-grid (custom-shell) forms had ~36px DOUBLE field spacing (per-field margin-bottom STACKED on the container flex gap) — .mfp .mf-field-group margin-bottom:0 lets the shell gap own spacing (→16px). AssetVersion→20260626-B287. Includes v1.7.32 builder template-gallery regression fixes.
    PREVIOUS v1.7.32 (20260626) — ⭐FIX builder template-gallery regressions (Oqtane fullscreen): (1) "Template Preview" pane was BLANK — the loader's inline live-form suppressor (scan()) cloaked the in-memory preview .mf-form-wrapper because the preview modal is a body-level [data-mf-overlay] OUTSIDE the builder root; scan() now skips wrappers inside [data-mf-overlay]. (2) "Upload Template" file dialog didn't open for users on a stale cached builder.js — the loader's BUILDER_BUNDLE_VERSION was a HARDCODED constant ('20260626-B244') that never busted the cache when builder.js was rebuilt; it now derives from the loader's own ?v (= AssetVersion), so one AssetVersion bump busts loader + builder + builder CSS together. AssetVersion→20260626-B284. Includes v1.7.31 — ⭐COMPLETE LANGUAGE PACKS + drift guard. Fixed incomplete i18n in the package: js/plugins/i18n was stale (1189 keys) and top-level js/i18n was absent — both now carry the full canonical catalog (1268 keys × 18 locales), matching js/builder/i18n + js/bundles/i18n. Root cause: pack.cmd never ran the i18n platform-sync, so the wwwroot wildcard shipped partial packs. Fix is permanent: i18n-sync-platforms.cjs now covers all four Oqtane i18n dirs (auto-creating missing ones), and pack.cmd runs it + a verify-package-complete.cjs guard that ABORTS the pack if any i18n/KB directory is incomplete. KB (34 TemplateGuides .md + 8 PromptRecipes via wwwroot, ai-knowledge-seed.json + RazorWidgets embedded in the DLLs) and SQL (EF migrations in the Server DLL) verified complete. AssetVersion→20260626-B283. Carries v1.7.30 settings-popup trim + v1.7.29 i18n/popup. dropped the redundant subtitle line, the duplicate inner "Module form" label (the accordion header already says it), and the clean-state "Active preset: …" line (dupe of the header meta). AssetVersion→20260626-B282 (cache-bust). Builds on v1.7.29 — ⭐SETTINGS PANE: i18n + POPUP. The in-page ⚙ Settings UI (Module form / Theme &amp; Layout / Theme preset / Layout / Page integration) is now (1) fully localized — ~67 new vd.set.* keys wired through the runtime catalog with REAL translations for all 11 maintained locales + Vietnamese (was 100% hardcoded English), and (2) opens as a TRUE centered popup with a dim backdrop instead of an inline pane. Also closed the i18n drift gate: +12 missing subs.* "Send to Inbox" keys added + translated (gate back to PASS). Inherits v1.7.28 clean-host install fix (all MF_* tables created on a fresh host).</releaseNotes>
    <summary>Dynamic form builder module for Oqtane CMS</summary>

    <packageTypes>
      <!-- "Dependency" is the standard NuGet library type — confirmed working by CISS.SideMenu reference -->
      <packageType name="Dependency" />
      <!-- Oqtane.Framework: minimum compatible framework version — read by InstallationManager XPath -->
      <packageType name="Oqtane.Framework" version="6.1.2" />
    </packageTypes>

    <dependencies>
      <group targetFramework="net9.0" />
    </dependencies>
  </metadata>
  <files>
    <!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
         COMPLETENESS (verified in v1.7.27): this package is COMPLETE for a clean Oqtane install —
         · DLLs: all MegaForm assemblies (Client/Server/Shared/Core/Sdk) + non-host deps
           (Newtonsoft.Json, Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.Language, Microsoft.CodeAnalysis[.CSharp]),
           for BOTH net9.0 and net10.0 (entries below).
         · KBs / SQL scripts: the wwwroot wildcard ships all KB content under
           wwwroot\Modules\MegaForm\Resources\ (34 TemplateGuide .md + PromptRecipes) + all js/css/
           fonts/img. The MF_* table "SQL scripts" are the EF migrations COMPILED INTO the Server DLL
           (Migrations\*.cs + EntityBuilders) — not standalone files — so they ship inside lib\*.
         ⭐ For a COMPLETE build, run the full `pack.cmd` (it npm-builds the 7 JS bundles + Vite-syncs
            them into MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\wwwroot BEFORE packing). A lean re-pack only refreshes
            what's already in that wwwroot — stale/missing bundles there → an incomplete package.
         ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <!-- net9.0 builds -->

    <!-- Client Blazor WASM DLL — tên chứa "Oqtane" → được load bởi IsOqtaneAssembly() -->
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Client\bin\Release\net9.0\MegaForm.Oqtane.Client.Oqtane.dll" target="lib\net9.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Client\bin\Release\net9.0\MegaForm.Oqtane.Client.Oqtane.pdb" target="lib\net9.0" />

    <!-- Server DLL — tên chứa "Oqtane" → được load -->
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net9.0\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server.Oqtane.dll" target="lib\net9.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net9.0\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server.Oqtane.pdb" target="lib\net9.0" />

    <!-- Shared DLL — tên chứa "Oqtane" → được load -->
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Shared\bin\Release\net9.0\MegaForm.Oqtane.Shared.Oqtane.dll" target="lib\net9.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Shared\bin\Release\net9.0\MegaForm.Oqtane.Shared.Oqtane.pdb" target="lib\net9.0" />

    <!-- Core DLL — tên KHÔNG chứa "Oqtane" → KHÔNG được load vào AppDomain -->
    <!-- Nhưng vẫn cần trong bin/ vì Client/Server DLL có reference đến nó -->
    <!-- .NET runtime sẽ tự resolve khi cần (dependency resolution) -->
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net9.0\MegaForm.Core.dll" target="lib\net9.0" />

    <!-- Third-party dependencies not provided by Oqtane host -->
    <!-- Newtonsoft.Json is used by MegaForm.Core; Oqtane 6 does NOT ship it -->
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net9.0\Newtonsoft.Json.dll" target="lib\net9.0" />
    <!-- [pkg-fix 20260625] MegaForm runtime deps the Oqtane host does NOT provide. Without these a
         CLEAN-host install crashes at startup (ReflectionTypeLoadException during Oqtane's assembly
         scan): MegaForm.Sdk → Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.Language → Roslyn (CodeAnalysis). The
         :5070 dev site only worked because it had accumulated them from earlier manual deploys. -->
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net9.0\MegaForm.Sdk.dll" target="lib\net9.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net9.0\Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.Language.dll" target="lib\net9.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net9.0\Microsoft.CodeAnalysis.dll" target="lib\net9.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net9.0\Microsoft.CodeAnalysis.CSharp.dll" target="lib\net9.0" />

    <!-- net10.0 builds (Oqtane 10.x hosts, e.g. :5070 Oqtane.MSSQL3 + :5000 Oqtane.New10) -->
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Client\bin\Release\net10.0\MegaForm.Oqtane.Client.Oqtane.dll" target="lib\net10.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Client\bin\Release\net10.0\MegaForm.Oqtane.Client.Oqtane.pdb" target="lib\net10.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net10.0\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server.Oqtane.dll" target="lib\net10.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net10.0\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server.Oqtane.pdb" target="lib\net10.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Shared\bin\Release\net10.0\MegaForm.Oqtane.Shared.Oqtane.dll" target="lib\net10.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Shared\bin\Release\net10.0\MegaForm.Oqtane.Shared.Oqtane.pdb" target="lib\net10.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net10.0\MegaForm.Core.dll" target="lib\net10.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net10.0\Newtonsoft.Json.dll" target="lib\net10.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net10.0\MegaForm.Sdk.dll" target="lib\net10.0" />
